#Text=Name a Pet
#Text=Naming a pet can be difficult considering all the cute names available .
#Text=When naming your pet you want to make sure their name is short and simple not something too crazy !
#Text=If you live with other people choose a name you all agree is fitting for your furry friend .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Think about your pet 's personality .
#Text=Does he/she remind you of a person , character , object , or s personality .
#Text=Is there an activity he/she loves to do ?
#Text=Is there a character trait that he/she reminds you of ?
#Text=Any of these could suggest a good name .
#Text=For example , is Star Wars a popular thing in your family ?
#Text=Maybe name your pet after Chewy or Leia !
#Text=Examine your pet .
#Text=Lets take a dog for example .
#Text=The dog is dark and reminds you of something you like .
#Text=You may name him/her Smoky or Stormy .
#Text=Maybe he/she smells a lot , so you could name him/her Stinky .
#Text=If you like cartoons , you may name him Pluto .
#Text=Be careful and choose wisely .
#Text=If you are naming a puppy or a kitten , pick a name that can grow with the pet as he ages .
#Text=Names such as Baby , Pups , or Bae for a child animal seem cute at the time , but when they grow to an adult , not so much .
#Text=Is your dog skinny or fat ?
#Text=Just because it is at the time you name it , does not mean in the future it will not loose/gain weight , so do n't name a pet Boney or Chubs .
#Text=Also avoid names that might alienate people , such as " Cujo , " which could remind others of the killer dog from the movie , " Cujo . "

column1: #Text=It 's also smart to nix names that are tongue twisters and that can be confused with training cues or everyday words .
#Text=" Mo , " for example , can be confused with " no , " " Tom " can be confused with " come , " and " Trey " can be confused with " stay . "
#Text=Think , do you want a common name ?
#Text=Maybe you think a common , usual , name will work bets for you dog .
#Text=Think of some names like Grace or Riley .
#Text=Max or Macy .
#Text=Jack , Tina , Biscuit , Kipper , Skipper , Noddle , or Bubbles .
#Text=Get a name book .
#Text=A name book that is used to help pick baby names can help you find a name !
#Text=Search through some names in the book .
#Text=Hey , who knows , you could find some very interesting names !
#Text=Get inspired by your own life .
#Text=Maybe name your pet " Joker " if you like comic books .
#Text=Do you collect or have interest in coins ?
#Text=Maybe name your pet Lincoln after the penny .
#Text=Avoid names that may be too long .
#Text=Example , the name Princess Peanut Butter is cute , but to long to say to your pet every minute or two .
#Text=Unless you plan to call the pet with the long name some quirky nickname like PPB , choose a name that is simpler that you could call the pet .
#Text=Warnings

#Text=Do n't use a name on your pet , especially if it is a dog or cat , for a prolonged period of time unless you are certain you will keep using it - deciding you do n't like the name a month down the line will just confuse the poor animal .
#Text=Do n't name your pet something derogatory or inappropriate .

#Text=It 's important to be courteous to others if you plan to call your pet in public , and it 's rude to expect your vet and his or her staff to use a derogatory name when you bring your animal in .
#Text=Do n't yell your pet 's name when your pet does something wrong .
#Text=Your pet may start associating his or her name with you being angry , especially if you do n't use the name much in other situations .
#Text=Just saying " no " is fine .
#Text=( Prevent problems and " bad habits " by using preventative measures , proper use of confinement , and training .
#Text=For example , a young healthy dog that barks a lot probably is bored and in need of mental , emotional and physical exercise .
#Text=Dog school , walks and hikes , and play dates with other nice dogs can make a noisy , constantly barking dog be a calm sleepy dog . )
